# Prework - Background Color

Submitted by: **Kim Singh**

**Name of your app** is an app that changes the background color when you click on a button.

Time spent: **2** hours spent in total

## Required Features

The following **required** functionality is completed:

- [done] Users can see a screen with three labels and a button
- [done] Tapping the button changes the screen color to a random color

## App Brainstorming (Step 4)

- Whatsapp
  - Simple UI, easy to navigate
  - Can call users over WiFi (VoIP)
- Instagram
  - Simple app that promotes socializing over photos
  - Reels are dopamine-inducing and can be quite funny
- Obsidian
  - Note taking app that allows for a lot of customizability
  - Can sync with laptop instantly and for free

- One app idea I would like to build is an app that allows users to download a local AI model, chat with it, take photos/videos, and interact with it however else they wish
  - Some features I would like to implement are:
    - Chat window
    - Live video interaction
    - Space to keep save messages
    - Simple and easy to navigate UI

## Notes

Describe any challenges encountered while building the app.

- Was difficult to navigate Xcode for the first time

